374
00:32:45.471 --> 00:32:46.961
Shotgun.

375
00:32:59.951 --> 00:33:01.680
Something the matter with the cuisine?

376
00:33:02.787 --> 00:33:04.687
Well. Mom. I'll tell you...

377
00:33:04.722 --> 00:33:08.249
when two of your friends die in the same day...

378
00:33:08.293 --> 00:33:10.420
let me know what it does to your appetite.

379
00:33:10.461 --> 00:33:11.587
You're just tired.

380
00:33:11.629 --> 00:33:14.564
Don't think I haven't noticed you aren't sleeping.

381
00:33:14.599 --> 00:33:17.796
That has got to stop. honey.

382
00:33:24.474 --> 00:33:26.203
What's wrong with me?

383
00:33:26.243 --> 00:33:28.074
Adolescent anxiety.

384
00:33:28.111 --> 00:33:29.601
That'll make it better.

385
00:33:35.485 --> 00:33:37.214
Oh. God.

386
00:33:37.254 --> 00:33:39.279
Mom. what did you do?

387
00:33:42.693 --> 00:33:45.287
Jesus! Sleeping pills?

388
00:33:46.663 --> 00:33:48.790
Look. Kristen. I'm sorry.

389
00:33:48.832 --> 00:33:50.299
Sorry?

390
00:33:50.334 --> 00:33:52.631
Sorry that you and your tennis pals...

391
00:33:52.668 --> 00:33:55.034
torched this guy. and now he's after me?

392
00:33:55.071 --> 00:33:58.370
In case you haven't been keeping score...

393
00:33:58.407 --> 00:34:02.002
it's his fucking banquet. and I'm the last course!

394
00:34:02.044 --> 00:34:04.842
We went over this in therapy!

395
00:34:04.880 --> 00:34:06.814
No. Mother.

396
00:34:06.849 --> 00:34:08.749
You just murdered me.

397
00:34:08.784 --> 00:34:11.378
Take that to your goddamn therapy.

398
00:34:58.966 --> 00:35:00.627
Dream someplace fun.

399
00:35:23.022 --> 00:35:25.115
Thanks. Alice.

400
00:35:28.294 --> 00:35:29.522
Hi. little girl.

401
00:35:31.864 --> 00:35:34.594
- What's your name?
- Alice.

402
00:35:34.634 --> 00:35:36.602
I have a friend named Alice.

403
00:37:33.281 --> 00:37:35.408
Elm Street's last brat.

404
00:37:35.449 --> 00:37:37.576
Farewell.

405
00:37:37.618 --> 00:37:39.643
We beat you before!

406
00:37:39.687 --> 00:37:43.214
And now you're all alone!

407
00:37:43.257 --> 00:37:46.988
Kristen. why don't you...

408
00:37:47.728 --> 00:37:49.787
call on one of your little friends?

409
00:37:49.830 --> 00:37:51.024
Maybe they could help.

410
00:37:51.065 --> 00:37:52.430
Never!

411
00:37:52.466 --> 00:37:54.763
I'm the last!

412
00:37:54.801 --> 00:37:57.235
Why don't you reach out...

413
00:37:57.270 --> 00:37:58.897
and cut someone?

414
00:38:18.758 --> 00:38:20.054
How sweet.

415
00:38:20.092 --> 00:38:22.060
Fresh meat.

416
00:38:26.932 --> 00:38:29.264
Alice. wake up and get out!

417
00:38:30.269 --> 00:38:31.564
Alice. I'm so sorry.

418
00:38:31.590 --> 00:38:32.794
It was a mistake.

419
00:38:32.838 --> 00:38:34.703
I pulled you in.

420
00:38:34.740 --> 00:38:37.641
Alice. come to Daddy.

421
00:38:37.676 --> 00:38:40.144
Leave her alone. you son of a bitch!

422
00:38:41.714 --> 00:38:44.478
Now no one sleeps.

423
00:38:50.288 --> 00:38:52.620
The souls of my children.

424
00:38:55.793 --> 00:38:58.387
You'll need my power.

425
00:39:32.996 --> 00:39:34.327
Are you OK?

426
00:39:35.565 --> 00:39:37.760
Kristen...
we've gotta get to her house!

427
00:39:59.455 --> 00:40:01.082
Oh. God! Kristen!

428
00:40:01.123 --> 00:40:03.353
Let me go.

429
00:40:23.545 --> 00:40:26.571
Hi. Alice.
Wish you were here.

430
00:40:26.614 --> 00:40:29.242
Your horrible brother's up to his old tricks.

431
00:40:29.284 --> 00:40:32.117
Rick. as long as I've known you. I've always wanted to ask...

432
00:40:32.153 --> 00:40:35.087
what the hell this shit is you put in your hair.

433
00:40:42.529 --> 00:40:43.791
I want his body.

434
00:40:43.831 --> 00:40:45.799
That's bullshit.
What else do you want?

435
00:40:45.833 --> 00:40:47.323
She wants my body.

436
00:40:51.839 --> 00:40:54.535
Alice. what are you doing?

437
00:40:56.477 --> 00:40:57.637
I don't know.

438
00:41:02.381 --> 00:41:04.349
It makes me feel better.

439
00:41:08.921 --> 00:41:10.388
What are you doing?

440
00:41:10.423 --> 00:41:12.254
Hello. baby.

441
00:41:12.291 --> 00:41:13.451
Great.

442
00:41:14.794 --> 00:41:16.557
You made her so happy then.

443
00:41:18.631 --> 00:41:20.792
Until all this Freddy shit.

444
00:41:22.468 --> 00:41:24.060
Why didn't I just stay with her?

445
00:41:24.103 --> 00:41:26.094
It wouldn't have made any difference.

446
00:41:26.139 --> 00:41:28.130
Sure it would have.

447
00:41:28.173 --> 00:41:32.701
No. I saw it happen in my dream.

448
00:41:34.679 --> 00:41:36.112
There was this horrible man.

449
00:41:38.650 --> 00:41:40.277
I don't wanna hear about Freddy. OK?

450
00:41:40.318 --> 00:41:43.253
I heard it all from Kristen. so stop it.

451
00:41:43.288 --> 00:41:46.280
I could smell the smoke.

452
00:41:46.324 --> 00:41:48.485
I could feel the heat from the fire.

453
00:41:48.527 --> 00:41:50.825
- It wasn't a dream!
- Just stop it!

454
00:41:51.830 --> 00:41:54.298
She wasn't crazy and neither are you...

455
00:41:54.332 --> 00:41:56.799
so just cut it out. Please.

456
00:41:58.469 --> 00:42:00.664
Jeez.
Why are you acting this way?

457
00:42:02.673 --> 00:42:04.163
I don't know. Rick.

458
00:42:05.242 --> 00:42:07.005
I just feel so different.

459
00:42:12.449 --> 00:42:14.644
Something happened in the dream.

460
00:42:15.953 --> 00:42:19.684
And now it's like part of her is with me.

461
00:42:26.129 --> 00:42:27.596
I love you. too!

462
00:42:27.630 --> 00:42:29.291
Hello. everyone!

463
00:42:32.235 --> 00:42:34.931
Girl. I am so dead on my feet.

464
00:42:34.971 --> 00:42:36.517
We have matching luggage.

465
00:42:36.543 --> 00:42:37.940
What do you mean?

466
00:42:37.974 --> 00:42:40.442
You didn't sleep last night?

467
00:42:40.476 --> 00:42:42.307
It's that obvious. huh?

468
00:42:42.345 --> 00:42:45.746
- Then you saw him. too.
- Saw who?

469
00:42:45.782 --> 00:42:48.046
I was up all night cramming for that physics test.

470
00:42:49.451 --> 00:42:52.113
Oh. and I put this little baby together.

471
00:42:52.154 --> 00:42:54.031
You know Deb's afraid of bugs.

472
00:42:54.057 --> 00:42:55.282
I made it for her.

473
00:42:55.324 --> 00:42:57.292
Ultrahigh sound waves.

474
00:42:57.326 --> 00:42:59.556
It'll make 'em run. screaming their antennas off.

475
00:43:01.830 --> 00:43:03.730
Look. I'll see you in class. OK?

476
00:43:15.777 --> 00:43:17.437
I don't smoke.

477
00:43:33.294 --> 00:43:36.752
All right. you've got forty minutes.

478
00:43:36.797 --> 00:43:39.493
So good luck. Go for it.

479
00:45:09.386 --> 00:45:10.717
Help me!

480
00:45:10.754 --> 00:45:11.880
Help!

481
00:45:11.922 --> 00:45:14.049
Wake up!

482
00:45:14.091 --> 00:45:15.251
Wake up. damn it!

483
00:46:09.344 --> 00:46:11.812
Wanna suck face?

484
00:46:16.951 --> 00:46:18.851
Sheila. wake up!

485
00:46:23.792 --> 00:46:25.554
You flunked.

486
00:46:33.967 --> 00:46:35.366
Give her her thing.

487
00:46:42.276 --> 00:46:44.013
Didn't you see it?

488
00:46:44.039 --> 00:46:45.268
He was here.

489
00:46:45.312 --> 00:46:46.779
What are you talking about?

490
00:46:46.814 --> 00:46:47.974
He was here!

491
00:47:10.002 --> 00:47:11.469
Step back. please.

492
00:47:11.504 --> 00:47:12.664
Stand back.

493
00:47:17.243 --> 00:47:19.335
Asthma attack?

494
00:47:21.913 --> 00:47:25.212
What 17-year-old has fatal asthma?

495
00:47:25.250 --> 00:47:28.219
God. she was gonna be a doctor.

496
00:47:28.253 --> 00:47:29.243
It was Freddy.

497
00:47:29.269 --> 00:47:31.222
Enough with that crap!

498
00:47:31.256 --> 00:47:34.384
I saw it. It was my dream.

499
00:47:34.426 --> 00:47:36.257
I brought Sheila in.

500
00:47:39.097 --> 00:47:41.224
Oh. God.

501
00:47:41.266 --> 00:47:44.235
I brought Sheila in like Kristen did with me.

502
00:47:44.269 --> 00:47:45.735
No. don't!

503
00:47:45.769 --> 00:47:47.566
I gave Sheila to him!

504
00:47:47.605 --> 00:47:49.664
And now she's dead!

505
00:47:53.777 --> 00:47:57.736
I really think Kristen's story is getting to her.

506
00:47:57.781 --> 00:48:00.750
Dan. I really don't know if it's a story.

507
00:48:00.784 --> 00:48:02.843
Look at us.

508
00:48:02.887 --> 00:48:04.787
We're dropping off like flies here.

509
00:48:43.258 --> 00:48:46.318
- Good seeing you.
- Bye.

510
00:48:46.361 --> 00:48:47.885
Come on.

511
00:49:10.718 --> 00:49:11.797
Excuse me. miss.

512
00:49:11.823 --> 00:49:13.576
Can I get a pack of gum?

513
00:49:16.691 --> 00:49:18.146
Hey. Where you been?

514
00:49:18.172 --> 00:49:20.183
I haven't seen you around.

515
00:49:20.228 --> 00:49:21.855
I've been working double shifts.

516
00:49:21.896 --> 00:49:24.126
Guess you need the extra money. huh?

517
00:49:24.165 --> 00:49:25.669
Look. you know why.

518
00:49:25.695 --> 00:49:28.149
You don't want to believe me.

519
00:49:30.738 --> 00:49:32.706
Don't you understand?

520
00:49:32.740 --> 00:49:34.707
I can't sleep.

521
00:49:34.741 --> 00:49:36.675
Someone might die.

522
00:49:48.088 --> 00:49:51.216
Let's say that this is real. right?

523
00:49:51.258 --> 00:49:54.386
Why. all of a sudden. is this Freddy guy after you?

524
00:50:01.433 --> 00:50:05.597
Kristen was the last child left of the people who killed Freddy.

525
00:50:07.473 --> 00:50:10.442
Maybe Freddy can't get to the new kids...

526
00:50:10.476 --> 00:50:12.808
unless there's someone to bring them to him.

527
00:50:17.416 --> 00:50:19.577
We're gonna be late for the drive-in.

528
00:50:19.618 --> 00:50:21.643
I have to get back.

529
00:50:25.291 --> 00:50:26.588
I guess I'll see you later.

530
00:50:39.237 --> 00:50:41.603
Ninety-three days till summer vacation. man.

531
00:50:41.639 --> 00:50:44.767
- You tired?
- No. Worried.

532
00:50:44.809 --> 00:50:46.777
Let's see if we can make it until summer.

533
00:50:46.811 --> 00:50:48.278
It's like open season around here.

534
00:50:48.313 --> 00:50:50.941
Pretty weird stuff.

535
00:50:50.982 --> 00:50:53.950
Speaking of weird. you gotta feel for that guy.

536
00:50:53.984 --> 00:50:56.782
Dead girlfriend. basket case for a sister...

537
00:50:56.820 --> 00:50:58.048
Shut up. asshole!

538
00:50:59.423 --> 00:51:01.357
What a dick.

539
00:51:01.391 --> 00:51:03.291
You know...

540
00:51:03.327 --> 00:51:04.794
You look wasted. man.

541
00:51:04.828 --> 00:51:06.796
I've been up with Alice.

542
00:51:06.830 --> 00:51:08.229
Hey. how's she doing?

543
00:51:08.265 --> 00:51:10.233
I saw her last night at the diner.

544
00:51:10.267 --> 00:51:12.235
She's blaming herself for Sheila.

545
00:51:12.269 --> 00:51:14.237
I know how she feels.

546
00:51:14.271 --> 00:51:16.739
I think about Kristen all the time.

547
00:51:16.773 --> 00:51:21.072
Maybe I could have stopped it if I'd have listened.

548
00:51:21.110 --> 00:51:22.577
You mean Freddy?

549
00:51:22.611 --> 00:51:24.238
What else?

550
00:51:24.280 --> 00:51:26.248
You ever take a look at our town's history?

551
00:51:26.282 --> 00:51:28.250
It's not exactly a safe place to be a teenager.

552
00:51:28.284 --> 00:51:30.844
Hey. bozos. let's hustle... now.

553
00:51:32.788 --> 00:51:35.780
Well. if I'm next. watch your back. man.

554
00:51:45.901 --> 00:51:47.391
Where were we?

555
00:51:49.304 --> 00:51:52.762
Every society. dating back to the ancients...

556
00:51:52.807 --> 00:51:55.275
has had theories regarding dreams.

557
00:51:55.310 --> 00:51:58.768
What they mean. how to control them.

558
00:51:58.813 --> 00:52:02.613
Aristotle believed during sleep your soul roams free.

559
00:52:02.650 --> 00:52:05.118
What it sees are dreams.

560
00:52:05.153 --> 00:52:08.213
The skilled dreamers are able to control what they see.

561
00:52:08.256 --> 00:52:11.589
There is a myth that there's two gates your soul can enter.

562
00:52:11.626 --> 00:52:14.220
One is a positive gate...

563
00:52:14.262 --> 00:52:16.456
the other a negative gate.

564
00:52:16.497 --> 00:52:19.557
The key element is that there's a dream master...

565
00:52:19.600 --> 00:52:21.727
someone who guards the positive gate...

566
00:52:21.769 --> 00:52:24.237
and. in fact. protects the sleeping host.

567
00:52:24.271 --> 00:52:27.729
Taken altogether. they offer a fascinating perspective...

568
00:52:27.775 --> 00:52:29.242
on ancient history.

569
00:52:29.276 --> 00:52:31.744
Those of you who don't find it fascinating...

570
00:52:31.779 --> 00:52:34.577
you better listen up. because it's on the final.

571
00:53:08.413 --> 00:53:11.473
Rick. make me laugh.

572
00:53:17.255 --> 00:53:19.416
Going down.

573
00:53:53.290 --> 00:53:54.621
What?

574
00:54:07.737 --> 00:54:11.264
A true warrior needs no eyes.

575
00:54:17.614 --> 00:54:20.174
Come on out and fight me. you chickenshit!

576
00:54:29.591 --> 00:54:32.890
Ninja warriors have calm.

577
00:54:32.928 --> 00:54:35.590
Find your balance. Rick!

578
00:54:37.766 --> 00:54:41.202
Too wimpy to show yourself. Krueger?

579
00:54:44.473 --> 00:54:46.304
Well. how's this for balance?

580
00:55:01.622 --> 00:55:03.180
Banzai.

581
00:55:06.127 --> 00:55:09.221
How you gonna fight me without your weapon. Freddy?

582
00:55:16.404 --> 00:55:18.338
Sayonara. Rick-san!

583
00:55:31.318 --> 00:55:33.115
Though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death...

584
00:55:33.153 --> 00:55:35.212
I shall fear no evil...

585
00:55:35.255 --> 00:55:37.587
for Thou art with me with Thy rod and Thy staff.

586
00:55:37.624 --> 00:55:40.092
They comfort me.

587
00:55:40.126 --> 00:55:44.028
Dearly bereaved. we gather here in remorse for Rick Johnson...

588
00:55:44.064 --> 00:55:47.898
a young man whose death confounds and mystifies us...

589
00:55:47.934 --> 00:55:51.300
for Rick was in his prime. beloved by all...

590
00:55:51.337 --> 00:55:53.601
exemplary of young men's ideals...

591
00:55:53.639 --> 00:55:55.869
and of strong moral fiber.

592
00:55:55.908 --> 00:55:59.844
We grieve our loss but take comfort in knowing such a man...

593
00:55:59.878 --> 00:56:01.846
rests in the kingdom of God.

594
00:56:01.880 --> 00:56:04.314
Let our faith supersede our knowledge...

595
00:56:04.350 --> 00:56:07.148
for truly the Lord works in mysterious ways.

596
00:56:10.022 --> 00:56:13.480
Hello. baby!

597
00:56:19.831 --> 00:56:22.061
I love this.

598
00:56:24.502 --> 00:56:27.471
They think I'm dead. don't they?

599
00:56:27.505 --> 00:56:29.268
This is great.

600
00:56:31.175 --> 00:56:34.076
Hey. What's with the tears?

601
00:56:34.112 --> 00:56:35.799
I wouldn't leave ya.

602
00:56:35.825 --> 00:56:37.570
Come on. don't cry.

603
00:56:37.615 --> 00:56:41.244
I'm here. It was a big joke to fool Freddy.

604
00:56:41.285 --> 00:56:43.344
Come on. smile for me.

605
00:56:44.554 --> 00:56:46.351
No more daydreams.

606
00:56:46.390 --> 00:56:49.359
Well. gotta go.

607
00:56:58.735 --> 00:57:00.202
Good night.

608
00:57:03.974 --> 00:57:05.339
You OK?

609
00:57:07.144 --> 00:57:08.475
Not really.

610
00:57:10.880 --> 00:57:12.973
Is there anything we can do?

611
00:57:13.015 --> 00:57:14.539
I don't think so.

612
00:57:16.485 --> 00:57:19.579
I guess this is my own war.

613
00:57:19.622 --> 00:57:22.147
No. it's not.

614
00:57:22.191 --> 00:57:25.627
We all have to survive.

615
00:57:25.661 --> 00:57:27.993
I mean. I don't spend hours working out...

616
00:57:28.030 --> 00:57:30.999
to let some night stalker beat me.

617
00:57:31.033 --> 00:57:33.263
You don't really get it.

618
00:57:33.302 --> 00:57:35.270
He's not a night stalker.

619
00:57:36.639 --> 00:57:39.971
And it'll take more than bench presses to beat him.

620
00:57:40.008 --> 00:57:42.067
So what do we do?

621
00:57:42.110 --> 00:57:43.668
Let's go over to Debbie's tonight.

622
00:57:43.712 --> 00:57:45.373
We have to make a plan.

623
00:57:47.515 --> 00:57:49.312
I got to go.

624
00:57:49.350 --> 00:57:51.341
How about I pick you up at the diner at 8:00?

625
00:57:53.588 --> 00:57:55.215
Here. It's a good luck charm.

626
00:57:55.256 --> 00:57:58.487
Brings bad luck to the creep you flatten with it.

627
00:57:58.526 --> 00:58:00.187
This is it.

628
00:58:01.396 --> 00:58:03.887
Mind over matter.

629
00:58:12.406 --> 00:58:14.636
Mind over matter?

630
00:58:17.111 --> 00:58:19.739
Sheila used to say that.

631
00:58:19.780 --> 00:58:23.147
God. every day. she changes.

632
00:58:23.183 --> 00:58:26.949
No. It's after every death.

633
00:59:43.661 --> 00:59:46.027
What's happening to me?

634
00:59:51.202 --> 00:59:53.692
Alice. where are you going?

635
00:59:53.736 --> 00:59:55.328
Just to see Debbie.

636
00:59:55.371 --> 00:59:56.633
No. you're not.

637
00:59:59.943 --> 01:00:01.911
I want you to stay in.

638
01:00:01.945 --> 01:00:05.642
Dad. I gotta go. and there's nothing you can do about it.

639
01:00:11.287 --> 01:00:13.949
You have no right to stop me.

640
01:00:17.327 --> 01:00:19.988
If you just knew what was going on.

641
01:00:20.028 --> 01:00:23.759
I know very much what's going on with you and your friends.

642
01:00:23.799 --> 01:00:28.259
Everybody thinks they know. but they don't.

643
01:00:28.303 --> 01:00:29.463
Look at me. Alice.

644
01:00:30.906 --> 01:00:34.535
I lost Rick because I didn't watch him.

645
01:00:34.576 --> 01:00:36.669
I don't want to lose you.

646
01:00:36.712 --> 01:00:38.441
We're all we have.

